{
  "texts": [
    "Steck and Jaakkola (2002) found that as ESS tends to zero, arc deletion is favoured producing sparser graphs.",
    "Similarly, Silander and Myllimaki (2006) observed that the number of arcs rose as ESS was increased.",
    "Ueno (2010) provided a detailed asymptotic analysis of BDeu supported by empirical experiments.",
    "This work showed that different elements of BDeu responded differently to ESS, with the complex behaviour heavily influenced by sample size and the skewness of the parameters.",
    "This work also showed that the K2 score approximates the BIC asymptotically as the sample size tends to infinity."
  ]
}